<div class="introduction f5">
  <h6 class="ttu tracked">Changing Input Type</h6>

  <p>So far, we have dealt with a simple text input. What about other forms of input?</p>

  <p>We can handle (mostly) everything. Here's a list of supported field types:</p>

  <ul>
    <li>text</li>
    <li>search</li>
    <li>url</li>
    <li>phone</li>
    <li>email</li>
    <li>number</li>
    <li>textarea</li>
  </ul>

  For example, if you want to make the editor a textarea, just pass in <code>textarea</code>
  to the <code>field</code> property.

  {{#x-card class="mt2" type="Code"}}
    {{code-snippet class="code f6" name="changing-input-type.hbs"}}
  {{/x-card}}

  <p>
    Here's what that will do.
  </p>

  {{#x-card type="Example"}}
    {{ember-inline-edit
      class="fl w-50"
      field='textarea'
      onSave=(action 'onSave' target=applicationController)
      value=(readonly value)}}
  {{/x-card}}
</div>
